Reasoning: This paper discusses a new inventory of semantic labels for adpositions and case markers, which is relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of machine learning and data analysis to develop this inventory also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the consideration of adposition and case phenomena in different languages may be of interest to researchers in neural engineering (cs.NE) and computer communication (cs.CC).
